    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AddressCoreExt

    public interface Address
extends com.guidewire.pl.domain.contact.gen.AddressStubI
    AddressBase Represents a street or mailing address. Addresses are normally associated with a Contact, either as a Primary Address for that Contact or via the ContactAddress table. Addresses can have geographic location information stored for proximity searches.

      • getCorrectionsFromGeocodingPlugin

        java.util.List<Address> getCorrectionsFromGeocodingPlugin()
        This gets a list of addresses which could match the provided address. The first result in the list is used as the best match found. This caps the number of results found.

        You can check if this is supported with a call to GeocodeUtils.currentPluginSupportsMultipleCorrections()

        Returns:
        A list of addresses. The first result returned will be the best match available.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if there is a problem connecting to the datasource.

      • getCorrectionsFromGeocodingPlugin

        java.util.List<Address> getCorrectionsFromGeocodingPlugin(int maxResults)
        This gets a list of addresses which could match the provided address. The first result in the list is used as the best match found. This caps the number of results found.

        Note that this DOES NOT modify the original address; if you want to use this in lieu of regular geocoding (ie geocodeSynchronously) you will have to copy over SpatialPoint and GeocodeStatus from the selected match.

        You can check if this is supported with a call to GeocodeUtils.currentPluginSupportsMultipleCorrections()

        Parameters:
        maxResults - the maximum number of results to return, if a positive/non-zero integer. Returns all results if zero or negative.
        Returns:
        A list of addresses. The first result returned will be the best match available.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if there is a problem connecting to the datasource.

      • getLatitude

        java.math.BigDecimal getLatitude()
        Latitude expressed in degrees. Positive = North; Negative = South: -90 <= x <= 90

      • getLongitude

        java.math.BigDecimal getLongitude()
        Longitude expressed in degrees relative to the prime meridian. Positive = East; Negative = West: -180 <= x < 180
